<dl id="un1013i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013i"> (NLI.3) 13(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cult of left hand (black magic) <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The <mark>&ldquo;cult of the left hand&rdquo;</mark> is, however, best known as a technical term in India, in use among the T&amacr;ntrikas, or practisers of the Tantras. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> The Left Hand way or Ritual is called the V&amacr;ma-M&amacr;rga, and a V&amacr;m&amacr;charin is a Practitioner of the Left Hand ritual or doctrine of the Tantras,&mdash;i.e., the worship of the Shakti or Feminine Power, the Power of Mother Nature (which has therefore to do with all nature and elemental powers) personified as the wife of Shiva&mdash;according to the grosser system, in which taking of drugs, sexual immorality and perversions and sorceries of all kinds, are practised. <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#THRdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), G. R. S. M., &ldquo;Queries and Notes. VI&rdquo; 368</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Copied to <a name="s15021ak" href="s15all.htm#s15021ak">Sheet 15.021(ak)</a>. </mm> </dd></dl>
